title: Monism, Atheism, and the Naturalist World-View: Perspectives fro
description: This is a 278 page thesis paper written by Greg Graffin, who you may know as the lead singer of Bad Religion, to get his PhD in zoology from Cornell University. Any fan of his music should find it very interesting, to say the least. If you don&#039;t feel like reading 278 pages, just read the interviews he has with some of the world&#039;s leading experts in evolutionary biology. He also published a book based on the project, titled "Is Belief in God Good, Bad, or Irrelevant?"
